<br>
So where does that leave you?  You can make friends with people on the rotations, so that when they're up for a dragon and are short a bard, someone will say &quot;hey!  maybe Skarklim is available!&quot;  (No guarantee that you'd be in the running for scales even then--many guilds have &quot;no loot for guests&quot; policies.)  You can save your coppers and buy your scales.  You can ask your guild leader to head on over to KGC and add your guild/alliance to the dragon rotations (assuming your guild/alliance has enough oomph to succeed).  Or you can go on KCoG raids when they reach the top of the rotation.<br>
<br>
Not trying to discourage you here, just laying out your options.<br>
<br>
Best of luck to you--the bard epic is not an easy one (personal experience here--my RL husband is an epic'ed bard).<br>
